"Flower, what happened?" I ask her.

"I... think I went a little overboard with the teleporting..." she says. "Give me a minute... I'm trying to recover."

"You do not have a minute, I'm afraid," the king of the underground says, as he traps us inside a semi-transparent box again and Peter begins to freeze the air inside it. "That is to say... unless your friend Barry can pull another rabbit out of his hat and come up with a teleportation spell of his own in the next fifteen seconds, of course. I have to admit that nothing coming from him would surprise me anymore at this point."

 While the king is talking, I am not processing any of his words, because my mind is too busy going through every single spell I've ever learned in a matter of seconds, in a desperate attempt to figure out if there's anything at all that could help me get out of this situation alive. While my head is filled with hundreds of possible combinations of spells, I can slowly feel the cold creeping in, until my whole body is trembling uncontrollably.

