TEXT:

#if(v_b3_ch9_backup == 0) {
 "So, what are you going to tell Daren, then?..." Flower says. "I thought we both promised him that we'd try our best to keep all casualties to a minimum."

}
#if(v_b3_ch9_backup == 1) {
 "The Overseer protocol would like to point out that it does not appreciate the fact that you didn't consider consulting it before making such an important decision," the green-eyed drone says. "The king of the underground and Peter could have both been used as valuable hostages if they were to be kept alive. Please refrain from taking such rash actions in the future if you do not want to put any more unnecessary strain on our already fragile alliance."

"Duly noted," I tell the Overseer.

"So, what are you going to tell Daren, then?..." Flower says. "I thought we both promised him that we'd try our best to keep all casualties to a minimum."

}
#if(v_b3_ch9_backup == 0 || v_b3_ch9_backup == 1) {
 They're both our enemies. They need to be killed. I'm sure they would have done the same thing to us if given the chance.

"Phew!" Flower says, as she is now using her fire jets to fly closer to me. "I almost thought we weren't gonna make it, for a second there... Nice work, Barry!"

While Flower was talking, I was busy conjuring two large stone plates on opposite sides of the king of the underground's head, positioning them approximately six feet away from him in both directions. Once I was done with that, I did the same thing for Peter, with two additional stone plates.

"Umm, Barry?..." Flower asks, looking a little nervous. "What are you planning to do with those rocks?..."

I ignore Flower and I raise my hands, taking control of both pairs of stone plates at the same time. Then, before Flower has the time to say anything else, I clap my hands as hard as I can and the two pairs of stone plates close in on each other at breathtaking speeds, turning the heads of both rebels into a thick red paste upon collision.

"NO!!!" Flower shouts, as she instinctively flies towards the dead bodies, even if she probably already realized that there's nothing she can do to help them anymore.

She cancels her fire jets a few seconds later when she comes back to her senses, and then she just stares at the lifeless bodies in front of her for a short while before she speaks again.

 "You killed them..." Flower says, looking as if she were still trying to accept the reality in front of her. "Why?..."

"They were too dangerous to be left alive," I say. "I had no choice."

"No choice?..." Flower says, incredulous. "They were both unconscious! We could have easily captured them!"

"Captured them how?" I ask. "Both of them could use powerful techniques without moving, so it's not like we could have just tied them up."

"I don't know!" Flower says. "We could have asked the Overseer to put them in an anti-magic prison cell or something! Wasn't that one of the main reasons why we allied ourselves with him?"

"It would have been too risky," I say. "We barely managed to beat them this one time. If they escaped from their cells, there was no guarantee that we could have beaten them again. Killing them was the only way to make sure that we wouldn't need to fight them anymore."

}
